sy%20shopping%20center%20in%20Chula%20Vista%2C%20California%2C%20and%20parked%20it%20outside%20of%20a%20Starbucks.%20There%2C%20an%20undercover%20agent%2C%20Special%20Agent%20Ronaldo%20Gonzalez%2C%20had%20a%20plan%20to%20make%20a%20sale.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20intended%20buyers%2C%20members%20of%20a%20known%20drug-trafficking%20organization%2C%20fell%20through%2C%20a%20contact%20helped%20him%20find%20another%20last-minute%20option%2C%20according%20to%20court%20documents.%20First%2C%20the%20contact%20showed%20up%20with%20two%20unknown%20potential%20buyers%2C%20whom%20Gonzalez%20later%20described%20as%20%26quot%3Bkids%2C%26quot%3B%20then%20two%20more%20young%20people%20appeared.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20Gonzalez%20opened%20the%20van's%20door%20to%20get%20out%20some%20product%2C%20he%20heard%20a%20commotion%20and%20spun%20around.%20He%20later%20told%20the%20Chula%20Vista%20police%20that%20he%20saw%20one%20of%20the%20young%20people%2C%20later%20identified%20as%20Fernando%20Llanez%2C%2022%2C%20aiming%20a%20black-and-yellow%20weapon%20his%20way.%20Within%2010%20seconds%20Gonzalez%20had%20shot%20Llanez%20four%20times%2C%20killing%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20fourth%20and%20fatal%20bullet%2C%20according%20to%20an%20excerpt%20of%20the%20autopsy%20cited%20in%20the%20complaint%2C%20entered%20Llanez's%20back%2C%20after%20he%20had%20already%20collapsed%2C%20face%20down%2C%20on%20the%20asphalt%2C%20and%20lodged%20in%20his%20tongue.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELlanez's%20weapon%20turned%20out%20to%20be%20a%20Taser.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221508%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20autopsy%20report%2C%20cited%20in%20a%20court%20record%2C%20reads%20in%20part%2C%20%26quot%3BA%20gunshot%20entrance%20would%20is%20located%20on%20the%20right%20mid%20back%26quot%3B%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66b3f132955b01c3294cc87f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22754%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAn%20autopsy%20report%2C%20cited%20in%20a%20civil%20complaint%2C%20finds%20that%20the%20fatal%20shot%20fired%20by%20ICE%20agent%20Ronaldo%20Gonzalez%20hit%20Llanez%20in%20the%20back%20after%20he%20had%20already%20collapsed.%3Cp%3EUS%20District%20Court%20for%20the%20Southern%20District%20of%20California%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20were%20just%20a%20bunch%20of%20kids%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Jorge%20Hernandez%2C%20an%20attorney%20who%20represented%20the%20Llanez%20family.%20%26quot%3BThis%20guy%20wasn't%20in%20uniform.%20The%20kid%20that%20got%20shot%20never%20knew%20he%20was%20a%20cop.%20Never%20flashed%20a%20badge.%20Never%20disclosed.%20Nothing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20young%20people%20Gonzalez%20approached%20weren't%20the%20target%20of%20the%20sting%20operation%2C%20according%20to%20a%20civil%20complaint%20Hernandez%20later%20filed.%20Once%20a%20situation%20becomes%20unpredictable%2C%20Hernandez%20said%2C%20agents%20typically%20call%20a%20sting%20off.%20But%20in%20this%20case%2C%20he%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bthey%20never%20called%20it%2C%20so%20it%20escalated.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20much%20could%20have%20gone%20differently%20that%20day%20in%20Chula%20Vista.%20Gonzalez%20could%20have%20identified%20himself%20as%20a%20law-enforcement%20officer.%20Or%20he%20could%20have%20tried%20to%20de-escalate%20the%20situation.%20But%20the%20Llanez%20family%20never%20learned%20whether%20Gonzalez%20had%20followed%20ICE%20training%20protocols%2C%20because%20the%20way%20ICE%20agents%20are%20trained%20has%20been%20largely%20hidden%20from%20the%20public.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMiguel%20Alvarez%2C%20an%20ICE%20spokesperson%2C%20said%20the%20agency%20does%20not%20comment%20on%20investigations%20or%20litigation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221324%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20excerpt%20of%20a%20civil%20complaint%20that%20reads%20in%20part%20%26quot%3BLLANEZ%20dies%20without%20ever%20knowing%20he%20had%20been%20shot%20by%20an%20officer%26quot%3B%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66b3ef68955b01c3294cc84c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22754%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20civil%20complaint%20filed%20by%20the%20Llanez%20family%20says%20that%20Gonzalez%2C%20the%20ICE%20agent%2C%20did%20not%20identify%20himself%20as%20a%20law%20enforcement%20officer%20before%20opening%20fire.%3Cp%3EUS%20District%20Court%20for%20the%20Southern%20District%20of%20California%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EA%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fimmigration-customs-enforcement-ice-agents-deadly-force-shootings-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ejoint%20investigation%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20Business%20Insider%2C%20The%20Trace%2C%20and%20Type%20Investigations%20identified%20Llanez%20as%20one%20of%2023%20people%20killed%20by%20ICE%20officers%20from%202015%20to%202021%2C%20with%20dozens%20more%20injured.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Department%20of%20Homeland%20Security%20requires%20its%20member%20agencies%2C%20including%20ICE%2C%20to%20minimize%20the%20risk%20of%20injury%20and%20risk%20to%20the%20public%2C%20and%20its%20amended%202023%20use-of-force%20policy%20requires%20officers%20to%20be%20proficient%20in%20de-escalation%20tactics.%20But%20ICE%20has%20never%20explained%20publicly%20how%20it%20prepares%20agents%20before%20sending%20them%20in%20the%20field.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20years%2C%20civil-rights%20groups%20have%20sought%20to%20obtain%2C%20with%20limited%20success%2C%20complete%20ICE%20training%20documents%20to%20understand%20how%20that%20training%20affects%20use%20of%20force%20by%20agents%20in%20the%20field.%20Business%20Insider%20and%20Type%20Investigations%20have%20now%20obtained%20hundreds%20of%20pages%20of%20previously%20unreported%20ICE%20training%20materials%2C%20including%20PowerPoint%20presentations%2C%20lesson%20plans%2C%20quizzes%20and%20answer%20sheets%2C%20and%20transcripts%20of%20multimedia%20presentations.%20None%20of%20the%20training%20documents%20we%20obtained%20address%20how%20to%20de-escalate%20tense%20or%20dangerous%20situations%20and%20avoid%20the%20use%20of%20force.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20the%20materials%20may%20have%20since%20been%20updated%20%E2%80%94%20they%20are%20dated%20from%202006%20to%202011%2C%20and%20ICE%20revised%20its%20training%20program%20in%202015%20and%202022%20%E2%80%94%20and%20do%20not%20represent%20a%20complete%20training%20curriculum%2C%20they%20offer%20the%20first%20in-depth%20look%20at%20training%20that%20shaped%20a%20generation%20of%20ICE%20agents%2C%20including%20Gonzalez%2C%20who%20was%20hired%20in%202006.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Caside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERead%20more%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fimmigration-customs-enforcement-ice-agents-deadly-force-shootings-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EArmed%20and%20untouchable%3A%20ICE's%20history%20of%20deadly%20force%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Faside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20couldn't%20find%20any%20guidance%20requiring%20immigration%20agents%20to%20identify%20themselves%20to%20suspects%20before%20using%20deadly%20force.%20And%20they%20also%20appear%20to%20place%20an%20emphasis%20on%20teaching%20ICE%20agents%20how%20to%20justify%20the%20use%20of%20force.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIv%C3%B3n%20Padilla-Rodr%C3%ADguez%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20history%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Illinois%20Chicago%20who%20studies%20child%20migration%20and%20labor%20trafficking%2C%20said%20that%20the%20public%20has%20a%20stake%20in%20how%20immigration%20agents%20are%20trained.%20%26quot%3BThey%20operate%20with%20a%20lot%20of%20impunity%20and%20a%20lot%20of%20discretion%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Band%20that%20ends%20up%20in%20the%20death%20of%20immigrants.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlvarez%2C%20the%20ICE%20spokesperson%2C%20said%20by%20email%20that%20the%20agency's%20officers%20%26quot%3Bare%20committed%20to%20protecting%20the%20homeland%20with%20the%20utmost%20integrity%26quot%3B%20and%20its%20leaders%20%26quot%3Breinforce%20standards%20of%20ethical%20and%20responsible%20conduct%20to%20further%20build%20and%20maintain%20public%20trust.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Deadly%20force%20can%20be%20initiated%20immediately'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20ICE%20officers%20are%20trained%20at%20sites%20in%20Charleston%2C%20South%20Carolina%2C%20or%20Glynco%2C%20Georgia%2C%20run%20by%20the%20Federal%20Law%20Enforcement%20Training%20Centers%2C%20a%20division%20of%20the%20Department%20of%20Homeland%20Security.%20There%2C%20FLETC%20offers%20aspiring%20agents%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fletc.gov%2Funiformed-police-training-program%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebasic%20law-enforcement%20training%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20includes%20use-of-force%20training%2C%20from%20how%20to%20respond%20to%20threats%20to%20writing%20up%20incident%20reports%3B%20firearms%20training%20such%20as%20proper%20handgun%20and%20rifle%20use%2C%20shooting%20positions%2C%20and%20live-fire%20cover%3B%20and%20legal%20training%2C%20covering%20rules%20of%20evidence%2C%20officer%20liability%2C%20and%20courtroom%20testimony.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmong%20the%20most%20important%20lessons%20ICE%20agents%20receive%20is%20when%20and%20how%20to%20use%20deadly%20force.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20found%20no%20lessons%20teaching%20strategies%20for%20de-escalation.%20To%20the%20contrary%2C%20some%20lessons%20appeared%20to%20encourage%20the%20agents%20to%20use%20force%20quickly%20and%20decisively.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20publicly%20available%20use-of-force%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fletc.gov%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2F2016%2520UOF%2520Podcasts.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etraining%20document%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20from%202016%2C%20said%20it%20was%20a%20myth%20that%20use%20of%20deadly%20force%20could%20be%20used%20only%20as%20a%20last%20resort%2C%20regardless%20of%20agency%20policy.%20%26quot%3BObjective%20reasonableness%20is%20the%20law%3B%20not%20policy%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20document%20reads.%20%26quot%3BUsing%20the%20minimal%20force%2C%20exhausting%20all%20lesser%20means%20of%20force%2C%20or%20always%20giving%20a%20warning%20could%20create%20an%20unnecessary%20risk%20for%20the%20officer.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221033%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20section%20of%20an%20ICE%20agent%20training%20document%20features%20a%20photo%20of%20a%20man%20in%20uniform%20firing%20a%20weapon%20at%20another%20person.%20The%20text%20reads%20in%20part%20%26quot%3BUsing%20the%20minimal%20force%2C%20exhausting%20all%20lesser%20means%20of%20force%2C%20or%20always%20giving%20a%20warning%20could%20create%20an%20unnecessary%20risk%20for%20the%20officer.%26quot%3B%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66b3f004955b01c3294cc859%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22678%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EOne%20use-of-force%20training%20document%20used%20by%20Federal%20Law%20Enforcement%20Training%20Centers%2C%20the%20agency%20that%20trains%20ICE%20agents%2C%20says%20it%20is%20a%20myth%20that%20deadly%20force%20can%20only%20be%20used%20as%20a%20last%20resort.%3Cp%3EFederal%20Law%20Enforcement%20Training%20Centers%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20exactly%20what%20attorneys%20for%20Special%20Agent%20Gonzalez%20argued%20in%20court%2C%20when%20the%20Llanez%20family%20filed%20suit.%20%26quot%3BIt%20is%20well%20settled%20that%20an%20officer's%20use%20of%20deadly%20force%20is%20reasonable%20where%20he%20had%20probable%20cause%20to%20believe%20that%20the%20suspect%20posed%20an%20immediate%20and%20serious%20threat%20to%20his%20safety%20or%20the%20safety%20of%20others%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20motion%20to%20dismiss%20reads.%20It%20was%20an%20argument%20that%20persuaded%20a%20federal%20judge%2C%20who%20dismissed%20the%20case.%20(Gonzalez%20didn't%20face%20criminal%20charges%20either%2C%20Hernandez%2C%20the%20family's%20attorney%2C%20said%2C%20though%20Alvarez%2C%20the%20ICE%20spokesperson%2C%20declined%20to%20confirm%20that.%20Gonzalez's%20lawyers%20at%20the%20Department%20of%20Justice%20declined%20to%20comment.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECitizens%20have%20the%20right%20to%20bear%20arms%2C%20the%20lesson%20goes%20on%20to%20say%2C%20but%20if%20an%20officer%20orders%20someone%20to%20put%20down%20their%20weapon%20and%20that%20order%20isn't%20followed%2C%20officers%20%26quot%3Bare%20not%20required%20to%20wait%20for%20someone%20to%20take%20a%20bead%20on%20them.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmong%20the%20documents%20we%20obtained%20is%20a%20lengthy%20set%20of%20quizzes%2C%20including%20more%20than%20100%20multiple-choice%20questions%2C%20with%20answer%20keys.%20Only%20one%20set%20of%20five%20questions%20deals%20with%20use%20of%20force.%20One%20of%20the%20questions%20asks%20which%20steps%20an%20officer%20must%20take%20before%20initiating%20deadly%20force%3B%20the%20answer%20is%20%26quot%3BNone%2C%20deadly%20force%20can%20be%20initiated%20immediately.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlvarez%2C%20the%20ICE%20spokesperson%2C%20disputed%20these%20findings%2C%20saying%20officers%20and%20agents%20are%20%26quot%3Btrained%20to%20only%20use%20force%20as%20a%20last%20resort%20when%20objectively%20reasonable%20and%20necessary%2C%20and%20to%20leverage%20de-escalation%20tactics.%26quot%3B%20He%20said%20ICE%20officers%20are%20regularly%20retrained%2C%20and%20any%20violation%20of%20policy%20is%20investigated%20thoroughly.%20ICE's%20basic%20training%20program%2C%20he%20said%2C%20added%20more%20emphasis%20on%20de-escalation%20in%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFLETC%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20detailed%20queries%20about%20how%20ICE%20agents%20are%20trained.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221475%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20excerpt%20from%20an%20ICE%20agent%20training%20document%20that%20reads%20in%20part%20%26quot%3BNone%2C%20deadly%20force%20can%20be%20initiated%20immediately%26quot%3B%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66b3f051955b01c3294cc85e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22754%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20training%20document%20with%20multiple%20choice%20questions%20and%20answer%20keys%20asks%20which%20steps%20an%20ICE%20officer%20must%20take%20before%20initiating%20deadly%20force.%20The%20answer%20is%20none.%3Cp%3EFederal%20Law%20Enforcement%20Training%20Centers%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20early%20as%202006%2C%20just%20three%20years%20after%20DHS%20was%20established%2C%20a%20basic-training%20instructor%20named%20John%20Bostain%20wrote%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fletc.gov%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Farchives%2F2006-Fall-FLETC-Journal.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFLETC%20trade%20journal%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20officers%20should%20be%20%26quot%3Bproactive%20rather%20than%20reactive%20in%20their%20application%20of%20force.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJim%20Trainum%2C%20who%20worked%20with%20the%20Metropolitan%20Police%20Department%20in%20Washington%2C%20DC%2C%20for%2027%20years%20and%20now%20offers%20criminal-case%20review%2C%20including%20on%20cases%20involving%20the%20use%20of%20force%20by%20federal%20officers%2C%20says%20that%20emphasis%20is%20not%20uncommon%20in%20law%20enforcement.%20%26quot%3BA%20lot%20of%20the%20training%20gives%20you%20excuses%20and%20justification%20for%20using%20force%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%202016%20shooting%20in%20Laurel%2C%20Mississippi%2C%20shows%20how%20this%20kind%20of%20training%20can%20play%20out%20in%20the%20field%2C%20and%20in%20the%20aftermath.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20a%20traffic%20stop%2C%20the%20local%20police%20called%20ICE%20agents%20to%20assist%20with%20translation.%20But%20one%20of%20the%20agents%2C%20Phillip%20Causey%2C%20ended%20up%20shooting%20a%20man%2C%20Gabino%20Ramos%20Hernandez%2C%20who%20wasn't%20even%20the%20subject%20of%20the%20stop.%20Ramos%2C%20an%20unauthorized%20immigrant%2C%20bolted%20once%20the%20ICE%20agents%20arrived%2C%20but%20then%20turned%20around%20to%20turn%20himself%20in%2C%20holding%20one%20hand%20up%20while%20he%20held%20up%20his%20pants%20with%20the%20other.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECausey%20told%20the%20court%20he%20opened%20fire%20because%20he%20suspected%20Ramos%20was%20reaching%20into%20his%20pants%20to%20retrieve%20a%20weapon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22878%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20excerpt%20from%20a%20court%20deposition%20that%20reads%20in%20part%2C%20%26quot%3BA.%20Sir%2C%20we%20don't%20fire%20warning%20shots.%20Q.%20You%20were%20shooting%20to%20kill.%26quot%3B%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66b3f0ae5da406397bf40ea1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22761%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EIn%20an%20August%202020%20deposition%2C%20an%20ICE%20agent%20named%20Phillip%20Causey%20was%20asked%20if%20he%20was%20shooting%20to%20kill%20when%20he%20fired%20at%20Gabino%20Ramos%20Hernandez.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20what%20we're%20taught%20to%20do%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3Cp%3EUS%20District%20Court%20for%20the%20Southern%20District%20of%20Mississippi%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EFour%20years%20later%2C%20on%20a%20humid%2C%2091-degree%20summer%20day%2C%20Ramos'%20lawyer%2C%20Timothy%20Cerniglia%2C%20met%20Causey%20at%20a%20federal%20courthouse%20for%20his%20deposition.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAt%20the%20time%20that%20you%20discharged%20your%20weapon%2C%20you%20weren't%20trying%20to%20fire%20a%20warning%20shot%2C%20were%20you%3F%26quot%3B%20Cerniglia%20asked.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSir%2C%20we%20don't%20fire%20warning%20shots%2C%26quot%3B%20Causey%20replied.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20were%20shooting%20to%20kill%2C%26quot%3B%20Cerniglia%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat's%20what%20we're%20taught%20to%20do%2C%26quot%3B%20Causey%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20judge%20dismissed%20the%20case%20Cerniglia%20brought%20for%20failing%20to%20show%20that%20Causey%20had%20violated%20Ramos'%20rights%3B%20the%20ruling%20is%20now%20being%20appealed.%20Though%20the%20Mississippi%20Bureau%20of%20Investigation%2C%20which%20investigated%20the%20shooting%2C%20brought%20charges%20to%20a%20grand%20jury%2C%20the%20jury%20chose%20not%20to%20indict.%20None%20of%20Causey's%20lawyers%20at%20the%20Department%20of%20Justice%20responded%20to%20requests%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlvarez%2C%20the%20ICE%20spokesperson%2C%20said%20ICE%20officers%20and%20agents%20are%20not%20trained%20to%20shoot%20to%20kill%2C%20but%20are%20trained%20to%20use%20deadly%20force%20only%20to%20stop%20whatever%20threatening%20behavior%20they%20face.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EEvading%20accountability%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20training%20documents%20we%20obtained%20appeared%20to%20focus%20more%20attention%20on%20evading%20accountability%20for%20use-of-force%20incidents%20than%20on%20how%20to%20avoid%20firing%20a%20weapon%20in%20the%20first%20place.%20They%20detail%20the%20factors%20courts%20consider%20when%20deciding%20whether%20use%20of%20force%20by%20a%20law-enforcement%20officer%20is%20justified%20and%20explain%20how%20agents%20should%20describe%20what%20they%20do%20in%20the%20field%20to%20survive%20legal%20scrutiny.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGood%20fact%20articulation%20helps%20the%20court%20make%20an%20objective%20decision%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20publicly%20available%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fletc.gov%2Fuse-force-part-i%23%3A~%3Atext%3DGood%2520fact%2520articulation%2520helps%2520the%2Cdecision%2520based%2520on%2520mere%2520conclusions.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elesson%3C%2Fa%3E%20reads.%20%26quot%3BWith%20facts%2C%20the%20court%20can%20visualize%20what%20happened.%20Facts%20'paint%20the%20picture.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20sample%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fletc.gov%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2FUOF%2520Test%2520-%2520Podcast%2520Transcript.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Equiz%3C%2Fa%3E%20led%20by%20an%20instructor%20in%20FLETC's%20legal%20division%2C%20called%20%26quot%3BUse%20of%20Force%20Test%3A%20Do%20You%20Know%20How%20You'll%20be%20Judged%3F%26quot%3B%20focuses%20on%20how%20a%20court%20might%20view%20an%20agent's%20remarks.%20Another%20quiz%2C%20on%20fugitive%20operations%2C%20asks%20students%20which%20legal%20standard%20allows%20for%20people%20to%20sue%20ICE%20for%20damages%20over%20violations%20of%20the%20Fourth%20Amendment%2C%20which%20prohibits%20unreasonable%20search%20and%20seizure.%20The%20transcript%20of%20a%20training%20lesson%20on%20officer%20liability%20outlines%20legal%20paths%20people%20can%20pursue%20to%20sue%20law-enforcement%20agents%20for%20misuse%20of%20power%2C%20wrongful%20use%20of%20force%2C%20or%20other%20forms%20of%20misconduct.%20%26quot%3BWe'll%20distinguish%20the%20different%20types%20of%20lawsuits%2C%20or%20civil%20actions%2C%20a%20law-enforcement%20officer%20could%20face%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20senior%20legal%20instructor%20says%2C%20%26quot%3Band%20we'll%20also%20discuss%20how%20to%20get%20out%20from%20under%20those%20lawsuits.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey're%20being%20taught%20what%20words%20to%20say%20to%20get%20around%20the%20letter%20of%20the%20law%20or%20circumvent%20the%20spirit%20of%20the%20law%2C%26quot%3B%20Trainum%20said.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20setting%20up%20the%20stage%20to%20tell%20a%20court%20I%20did%20what%20I%20had%20to.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20a%20December%202018%20podcast%20called%20%26quot%3BCareers%20at%20ICE%2C%26quot%3B%20produced%20by%20the%20agency%20for%20people%20interested%20in%20becoming%20an%20immigration%20officer%2C%20features%20a%20deportation%20officer%20named%20Christian%20Rodriguez.%20%26quot%3BNinety%20percent%20of%20our%20job%20is%20being%20able%20to%20articulate%20the%20reasons%20as%20to%20why%20we%20do%20what%20we%20do%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20%26quot%3BIf%20I%20train%20anybody%2C%20I%20say%2C%20'Chances%20are%20you're%20not%20going%20to%20get%20in%20trouble%20for%20what%20you%20do%20out%20in%20the%20field.%20You%20will%20get%20in%20trouble%20for%20your%20inability%20to%20articulate%20why%20you%20did%20what%20you%20did.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20scenario-based%20lesson%20called%20Team%20Tactics%2C%20dated%202007%2C%20guides%20agents%20on%20how%20to%20operate%20around%20the%20constraints%20of%20administrative%20warrants.%20In%20it%2C%20instructors%20teach%20ICE%20trainees%20how%20to%20extract%20consent%20to%20enter%20private%20property.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BStress%20verbal%20techniques%20that%20may%20be%20employed%20to%20coax%20the%20target%20out%20of%20the%20residence%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20notes%20read.%20When%20hoping%20to%20enter%20a%20place%20of%20business%2C%20they%20say%2C%20%26quot%3BStudents%20should%20apply%20verbal%20techniques%2C%20with%20the%20intent%20of%20having%20the%20manager%20grant%20consent.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lesson%20includes%20discussion%20of%20how%20a%20%26quot%3Bhot-pursuit%20scenario%26quot%3B%20may%20allow%20officers%20to%20engage%20in%20a%20warrantless%20search%20or%20arrest.%20%26quot%3BStress%20the%20factors%20the%20court%20will%20consider%20in%20determining%20exigency%20to%20justify%20a%20warrant%20less%20search%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20instructor%20notes%20read.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIncluding%20Causey%2C%20we%20identified%20seven%20ICE%20officers%20or%20agents%20named%20as%20defendants%20in%20lawsuits%20alleging%20misconduct%20over%20their%20use%20of%20firearms.%20One%20case%20was%20settled%20without%20admission%20of%20wrongdoing.%20Another%20case%20is%20still%20underway.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEvery%20other%20suit%20was%20dismissed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fice-immigration-customs-enforcement-training-deescalation-use-of-force-2024-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1723456981000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66b521bf5da406397bf44fa5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fice-immigration-customs-enforcement-tra