india.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fsouth-asia%2Fwill-try-to-bring-back-sheikh-hasina-if-bangladesh-interim-government%2Famp_articleshow%2F112465093.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fsouth-asia%2Fwill-try-to-bring-back-sheikh-hasina-if-bangladesh-interim-government%2Famp_articleshow%2F112465093.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Flying%20has%20never%20been%20worse%20%E2%80%94%20but%20hope%20is%20on%20the%20way%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Photo%20collage%20of%20a%20plane%20and%20cash.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66b22ba4393cd3c8629b84a3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20government%20is%20maybe%20going%20to%20make%20flying%20slightly%20less%20terrible.%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3B%20Jenny%20Chang-Rodriguez%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EI%20do%20not%20know%20anyone%20who%20heads%20to%20the%20airport%20and%20thinks%20to%20themselves%2C%20%26quot%3BOh%20man%2C%20I%20bet%20this%20is%20going%20to%20be%20an%20awesome%20experience.%26quot%3B%20Just%20booking%20a%20flight%20means%20contemplating%20a%20sliding%20scale%20of%20unfortunate%20scenarios.%20What%20if%20my%20bag%20is%20lost%3F%20What%20if%20the%20flight%20is%20overbooked%3F%20What%20do%20I%20do%20if%20it's%20delayed%20or%20canceled%3F%20Once%20you%20get%20to%20the%20airport%2C%20things%20only%20get%20worse%3A%20the%20headache%20that%20is%20maneuvering%20through%20long%20security%20lines%2C%20swallowing%20eye-popping%20airport%20prices%2C%20or%20wondering%20just%20how%20scared%20you%20should%20be%20if%20you%20wind%20up%20on%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fboeing-crashes-groundings-timeline-737-max-777-air-force-tanker-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBoeing%3C%2Fa%3E.%20At%20this%20point%2C%20it's%20more%20of%20a%20pleasant%20surprise%20if%20a%20flight%20actually%20goes%20as%20planned.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBeyond%20the%20low-level%20dread%20that%20accompanies%20every%20trip%2C%20several%20high-profile%20recent%20incidents%20have%20driven%20home%20how%20frustrating%20air%20travel%20can%20be.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fairline-expert-explains-whats-going-on-with-southwest-cancellations-2022-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESouthwest's%20December%202022%20meltdown%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20due%20in%20large%20part%20to%20its%20outdated%20scheduling%20system%2C%20resulted%20in%20nearly%2017%2C000%20flight%20cancellations%20and%20more%20than%202%20million%20stranded%20passengers.%20This%20summer%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdelta-canceled-more-flights-in-5-days-than-2-years-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDelta%20canceled%20thousands%20of%20flights%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20it%20struggled%20to%20recover%20from%20the%20CrowdStrike%20outage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20you%20set%20your%20passport%20on%20fire%20and%20declare%20that%20from%20here%20on%20out%20you'll%20only%20be%20hitting%20the%20great%20American%20highways%20for%20vacation%2C%20know%20that%20help%20is%20on%20the%20way.%20On%20the%20consumer%20front%2C%20the%20federal%20government%20is%20trying%20to%20make%20flying%20less%20disastrous%20where%20possible.%20It's%20making%20it%20so%20that%20when%20the%20airlines%20have%20an%20oops%2C%20they%20don't%20get%20to%20hold%20on%20to%20your%20money%20%E2%80%94%20and%20they%20can't%20wait%20until%20you%20have%20a%20hissy%20fit%20to%20give%20you%20a%20refund.%20In%20the%20wake%20of%20the%20pandemic%2C%20for%20example%2C%20the%20Department%20of%20Transportation%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.transportation.gov%2Fbriefing-room%2Fmore-600-million-refunds-returned-airline-passengers-under-dot-rules-backed-new%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etook%20action%3C%2Fa%3E%20against%20six%20airlines%20that%20dragged%20their%20feet%20on%20giving%20passengers%20over%20%24600%20million%20in%20refunds.%20The%20government%20is%20also%20trying%20to%20make%20airlines%20be%20up%20front%20about%20fees%20and%20ax%20some%20charges.%20The%20message%20to%20the%20airline%20industry%3A%20You've%20had%20a%20few%20too%20many%20screwups%20to%20be%20left%20to%20your%20own%20devices.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20goes%20through%20cycles%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Bob%20Mann%2C%20an%20aviation%20analyst.%20%26quot%3BAirlines%20behave%20badly%2C%20airlines%20behave%20badly.%20Customers%20react%2C%20customers%20react.%20Finally%2C%20the%20DOT%20reacts.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EWilliam%20McGee%2C%20a%20longtime%20consumer%20advocate%20and%20senior%20fellow%20for%20aviation%20and%20travel%20at%20the%20American%20Economic%20Liberties%20Project%2C%20an%20anti-monopoly%20think%20tank%2C%20is%20a%20guy%20who%20thinks%20%3Cem%3Ea%20lot%20%3C%2Fem%3Eabout%20all%20the%20problems%20with%20the%20airline%20industry.%20He%20was%20fairly%20unimpressed%20with%20President%20Joe%20Biden's%20administration%2C%20particularly%20Transportation%20Secretary%20Pete%20Buttigieg%2C%20for%20the%20first%20year%20or%20two%2C%20but%20now%20he's%20a%20fan.%20The%20airline%20industry's%20screwups%20in%20recent%20years%2C%20capped%20off%20by%20the%20Southwest%20debacle%2C%20were%20the%20%26quot%3Bturning%20point%26quot%3B%20that%2C%20in%20his%20view%2C%20got%20the%20administration%20to%20step%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI've%20seen%20more%20progress%20in%20the%20last%20year%20on%20consumer%20protections%20than%20I%20have%20%E2%80%94%20I'm%20not%20being%20hyperbolic%20%E2%80%94%20in%20the%20last%2015%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20past%20couple%20of%20years%2C%20the%20Biden%20administration%20has%20introduced%20a%20slew%20of%20rules%20and%20services%20intended%20to%20make%20airline%20passengers'%20lives%20easier.%20Some%20are%20aimed%20at%20protecting%20people's%20pocketbooks%2C%20others%20at%20just%20helping%20them%20stay%20informed%20about%20their%20options%20and%20rights.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20April%2C%20the%20DOT%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.transportation.gov%2Fbriefing-room%2Fbiden-harris-administration-announces-final-rule-requiring-automatic-refunds-airline%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eannounced%20a%20final%20rule%3C%2Fa%3E%20requiring%20airlines%20to%20automatically%20issue%20refunds%20when%20they%20cancel%20or%20significantly%20change%20flights.%20The%20rule%2C%20set%20to%20go%20into%20effect%20in%20October%2C%20also%20says%20airlines%20have%20to%20give%20people%20their%20money%20back%20on%20fees%20for%20other%20services%20when%20they%20are%20not%20delivered%20as%20promised%2C%20like%20if%20their%20checked%20bag%20gets%20super%20delayed%20or%20the%20plane%20WiFi%20they%20purchased%20doesn't%20work.%20Importantly%2C%20the%20DOT%20stipulates%20that%20the%20refunds%20have%20to%20be%20in%20cash%20or%20the%20original%20form%20of%20payment%20%E2%80%94%20no%20more%20vouchers%20or%20credits%20that%20lock%20up%20consumers'%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey've%20always%20been%20reluctant%20to%20give%20refunds%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Janet%20Bednarek%2C%20an%20aviation%20historian%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Dayton.%20%26quot%3BThey%20much%20prefer%20to%20keep%20your%20money%20and%20keep%20you%20as%20a%20customer%20by%20giving%20you%20a%20voucher%2C%20which%20can%20only%20be%20used%20on%20their%20company.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBiden%20signed%20the%20Federal%20Aviation%20Administration%20reauthorization%20bill%20in%20May%20that%20included%20the%20stipulations%20about%20automatic%20refunds%20for%20delayed%20and%20canceled%20flights%2C%20giving%20the%20DOT%20rule%20even%20more%20legislative%20bite.%20(The%20part%20of%20the%20rule%20specific%20to%20refunds%20on%20ancillary%20fees%20won't%20kick%20in%20until%20the%20fall.)%20Buttigieg%20also%20sent%20a%20reminder%20to%20airlines%20in%20July%20about%20their%20obligations%20on%20passenger%20refunds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20am%20hearing%20reports%20of%20some%20airlines%20only%20offering%20flight%20credits%20to%20passengers%20for%20cancelled%20flights%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote%20on%20X.%20%26quot%3BLet%20me%20be%20clear%20%E2%80%94%20you%20are%20entitled%20to%20get%20your%20money%20back%20promptly%20if%20your%20flight%20is%20cancelled%20and%20you%20don't%20take%20a%20rebooking.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20airline%20industry%20seems%20to%20be%20relatively%20on%20board%20with%20the%20refund%20idea.%20A%20spokesperson%20for%20Airlines%20for%20America%2C%20an%20industry%20trade%20group%2C%20told%20me%20in%20an%20email%20that%20its%20members%20%26quot%3Bstrongly%20support%26quot%3B%20rules%20requiring%20automatic%20refunds%20and%20that%20its%20carriers%20%26quot%3Babide%20by%20%E2%80%94%20and%20frequently%20exceed%20%E2%80%94%20DOT%20regulations%20regarding%20consumer%20protections.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20industry%20is%20not%20so%20on%20board%20with%20other%20parts%20of%20the%20Biden%20administration's%20make-flying-less-awful%20agenda.%20Major%20airlines%20and%20A4A%20have%20sued%20to%20challenge%20a%20DOT%20rule%20aimed%20at%20protecting%20consumers%20from%20what%20the%20administration%20has%20called%20%26quot%3Bjunk%20fees.%26quot%3B%20It%20would%20make%20the%20airlines%20tell%20consumers%20up%20front%20about%20extra%20charges%20for%20checking%20or%20carrying%20on%20bags%2C%20canceling%20a%20trip%2C%20or%20changing%20reservations.%20The%20industry%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20holds%20that%20disclosing%20fees%20immediately%20would%20%26quot%3Bgreatly%20confuse%20consumers%20who%20will%20be%20inundated%20with%20information%26quot%3B%20and%20that%20the%20DOT's%20efforts%20to%20regulate%20the%20charges%20are%20beyond%20its%20authority.%20(Courts%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthehill.com%2Fregulation%2Fcourt-battles%2F4800399-joe-biden-airline-junk-fees-rule-temporarily-paused%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etemporarily%20blocked%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20rule.)%20In%20essence%2C%20the%20DOT%20is%20arguing%20that%20airlines%20should%20be%20clear%20about%20their%20fees%20so%20that%20consumers%20can%20accurately%20compare%20prices%2C%20while%20the%20airlines%20are%20saying%20it's%20unnecessary.%20In%20an%20email%2C%20the%20A4A%20spokesperson%20argued%20that%20airlines%20already%20do%20enough%20to%20inform%20consumers%20about%20fees%20and%20described%20the%20rule%20as%20%26quot%3Ba%20bad%20solution%20in%20search%20of%20a%20problem.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20DOT%20has%20also%20proposed%20a%20rule%20that%20would%20bar%20airlines%20from%20charging%20a%20fee%20for%20parents%20to%20sit%20next%20to%20their%20kids.%20Some%20airlines%20already%20do%20this%20%E2%80%94%20but%20not%20all%20of%20them.%20A4A%20says%20all%20its%20carriers%20make%20%26quot%3Bevery%20effort%20to%20ensure%20families%20sit%20together%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20each%20has%20its%20own%20policy.%20The%20rule%20is%20now%20headed%20to%20a%20public-comment%20period%2C%20meaning%20it%20will%20be%20a%20while%20before%20it's%20finalized%2C%20if%20it%20ever%20is.%20The%20Biden%20administration%20is%20also%20trying%20to%20make%20flying%20specifically%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapnews.com%2Farticle%2Fairlines-wheelchairs-regulation-biden-administration-71be0f947702fd6e9dcdde97bd53b3ef%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebetter%20for%20people%20with%20disabilities%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20improve%20standards%20around%20accommodations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBeyond%20rulemaking%20and%20enforcement%2C%20the%20DOT%20has%20made%20some%20efforts%20to%20help%20consumers%20navigate%20various%20airlines'%20policies.%20It's%20launched%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.transportation.gov%2Fairconsumer%2Fairline-customer-service-dashboard%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edashboard%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20let%20you%20see%20which%20airlines%20offer%20services%20such%20as%20free%20family%20seating%20and%20free%20rebooking%20in%20the%20event%20of%20a%20%26quot%3Bcontrollable%26quot%3B%20cancellation%20or%20a%20long%20delay%2C%20meaning%20a%20problem%20caused%20by%20the%20airline.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20dashboard%20and%20the%20various%20rules%20about%20refunds%20are%20nice%20%E2%80%94%20knowledge%20is%20power%2C%20after%20all%20%E2%80%94%20but%20the%20effect%20is%20limited%20because%20not%20a%20lot%20of%20passengers%20know%20about%20them.%20Most%20Americans%20fly%20maybe%20once%20or%20twice%20a%20year%2C%20and%20even%20people%20being%20informed%20about%20the%20whole%20deal%20doesn't%20stop%20airlines%20from%20trying%20to%20first%20offer%20a%20voucher%20instead%20of%20a%20refund%20or%20charge%20their%20litany%20of%20fees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20guess%20it's%20better%20in%20that%20consumers%20have%20access%20to%20better%20information%2C%20but%20there%20is%20still%20a%20lot%20of%20push%20and%20pull%20out%20there%2C%26quot%3B%20Bednarek%20said.%20%26quot%3BHow%20many%20consumers%20actually%20go%20to%20that%20dashboard%20to%20find%20out%20how%20open%20are%20the%20airlines%20about%20what%20the%20rules%20actually%20are%3F%20How%20do%20you%20tell%20the%20difference%20between%20a%20controllable%20and%20an%20uncontrollable%20delay%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20McGee%20says%20the%20Biden%20administration's%20consumer-protection%20efforts%20have%20been%20admirable%3A%20%26quot%3BButtigieg%20has%20stepped%20up%2C%20and%20it's%20like%20there's%20a%20new%20sheriff%20in%20town%2C%20and%20the%20airlines%20don't%20like%20it%2C%20and%20they're%20very%20critical%20of%20him%2C%20and%20they're%20critical%20of%20Congress.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3ELike%20a%20lot%20of%20businesses%20and%20industries%2C%20airlines%20tend%20to%20overreact%20at%20the%20slightest%20hint%20of%20new%20rules%20and%20regulations%2C%20even%20just%20stuff%20at%20the%20margins.%20That%20seems%20to%20be%20a%20lot%20of%20what's%20happening%20here%20%E2%80%94%20none%20of%20what%20the%20administration%20is%20pushing%20is%20that%20dire.%20I%20can%20see%20the%20argument%20that%20listing%20fees%20out%20on%20a%20site%20like%20Expedia%20or%20Kayak%20might%20be%20a%20little%20jarring%20for%20consumers%20at%20first%2C%20but%20that%20should%20be%20a%20solvable%20user-experience%20problem.%20On%20the%20refunds%20thing%2C%20I%20mean%2C%20come%20on%20%E2%80%94%20if%20you%20order%20a%20burger%20at%20a%20restaurant%20and%20the%20restaurant%20is%20out%20of%20burgers%2C%20it%20doesn't%20get%20to%20charge%20you%20for%20the%20burger%20anyway.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20ask%20the%20industry%20to%20do%20something%2C%20they%20will%20first%20say%20it's%20impossible%2C%26quot%3B%20Mann%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20after%20making%20it%20clear%20that%20it's%20definitely%20not%20impossible%2C%20they%20will%20say%2C%20well%2C%20we%20could%20do%20that%2C%20but%20it%20would%20cause%20us%20irreparable%20harm.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EConsumers%20do%20have%20the%20opportunity%20to%20vote%20with%20their%20feet%20and%20go%20to%20better%20airlines%2C%20but%20there%20is%20a%20natural%20limit%20to%20this%2C%20given%20that%20almost%20every%20airline%20is%20experiencing%20hiccups%20and%20using%20many%20of%20the%20same%20tactics.%20Still%2C%20not%20everyone%20agrees%20with%20the%20government's%20meddling.%20George%20Ferguson%2C%20an%20airline%20analyst%20at%20Bloomberg%20Intelligence%2C%20told%20me%20he%20thinks%20the%20market%20should%20be%20able%20to%20sort%20itself%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20most%20other%20businesses%20in%20the%20US%2C%20the%20government%20doesn't%20step%20in%20and%20tell%20a%20business%20whether%20it%20has%20to%20give%20a%20refund%20or%20a%20credit%20or%20how%20that%20has%20to%20work%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BAs%20much%20as%20you%20could%20kind%20of%20see%20the%20airlines%20sitting%20on%20people's%20refunds%2C%20some%20of%20them%20split%20with%20the%20pack%3B%20some%20of%20them%20were%20better%20than%20others%20in%20getting%20refunds.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20many%20cases%2C%20however%2C%20it%20was%20hard%20to%20know%20which%20airline%20had%20which%20policy%2C%20and%20now%20whether%20and%20how%20fast%20you'll%20get%20your%20money%20back%20doesn't%20depend%20on%20the%20airline.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGetting%20a%20refund%20on%20a%20service%20that%20wasn't%20delivered%20seems%20like%20a%20bit%20of%20a%20gimme.%20But%20there%20are%20plenty%20of%20other%20problems%20with%20the%20airline%20industry%20that%20need%20solving%20%E2%80%94%20some%20the%20government%20can%20take%20care%20of%2C%20and%20some%20the%20government%20is%20causing.%20The%20FAA%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fair-traffic-controller-shortage-salary-requirements-plane-collisions-close-calls-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eshort%20thousands%20of%20air-traffic%20controllers%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20affects%20schedules%20and%2C%20if%20you%20really%20want%20to%20worry%2C%20potentially%20safety.%20The%20agency%20has%20dealt%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdelta-ceo-calls-faa-outage-unacceptable-says-needs-more-money-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etech%20headaches%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20has%20been%20accused%20of%20falling%20short%20on%20some%20of%20its%20oversight%20duties.%20The%20recently%20signed%20reauthorization%20bill%20should%20help%20in%20some%20areas%20%E2%80%94%20getting%20more%20air-traffic%20controllers%20and%20safety%20inspectors%20hired%2C%20for%20example%20%E2%80%94%20but%20the%20FAA%20still%20has%20its%20fair%20share%20of%20issues.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.gallup.com%2Fpoll%2F1579%2Fairlines.aspx%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGallup%20polls%20suggest%3C%2Fa%3E%20more%20Americans%20have%20a%20negative%20view%20of%20the%20airline%20industry%20than%20a%20positive%20one.%20But%20there%20are%20all%20sorts%20of%20ways%20flying%20can%20and%20should%20be%20better.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.vox.com%2F23460965%2Fairport-restaurant-flight-prices-lounge-bar-expensive%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAirport%20prices%20for%20things%20like%20food%20and%20beverages%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20whether%20a%20full%20meal%20or%20a%20simple%20cup%20of%20coffee%2C%20are%20truly%20outlandish.%20Flights%20are%20packed%20and%20often%20overbooked.%20The%20fees%20really%20are%20hard%20to%20figure%20out.%20The%20argument%20that%20airlines%20make%20is%20that%20it's%20a%20positive%20for%20passengers%20to%20be%20able%20to%20get%20the%20lowest%20price%20and%20then%20add%20on%2C%20but%20when%20the%20starting%20price%20for%20a%20ticket%20you%20see%20on%20a%20travel%20website%20winds%20up%20being%20%24100%20lower%20than%20the%20fare%20you%20wind%20up%20paying%2C%20it's%20annoying.%20The%20fees%20also%20create%20a%20bunch%20of%20weird%20incentives%20%E2%80%94%20everyone%20tries%20to%20board%20with%20their%20bags%20to%20avoid%20paying%20extra%2C%20and%20the%20planes%20just%20aren't%20made%20to%20accommodate%20everyone's%20bags.%20At%20a%20higher%20level%2C%20it's%20easy%20to%20wonder%20whether%20the%20airline%20industry%20is%20competitive%20enough%20or%20whether%20deregulating%20the%20airlines%20in%20the%201970s%20was%20really%20the%20right%20move.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20reality%20is%20also%20that%20the%20way%20the%20airlines%20get%20better%20%E2%80%94%20either%20because%20they%20decide%20to%20or%2C%20more%20often%2C%20because%20passengers%2C%20lawmakers%2C%20and%20regulators%20demand%20it%20%E2%80%94%20is%20often%20through%20a%20major%20screwup.%20Things%20get%20bad%20enough%20that%20finally%20there's%20some%20action.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAbsent%20the%20public%20failures%2C%20there%20wouldn't%20be%20a%20lot%20of%20political%20will%20to%20take%20these%20actions%2C%20Bednarek%20said.%20%26quot%3BYou%20say%2C%20OK%2C%20we%20can%20all%20agree%20that%20this%20was%20unacceptable.%20And%20the%20airlines%20themselves%20recognize%20that%20this%20could%20be%20damaging%20to%20their%20bottom%20line%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey%20will%20take%20action%2C%20and%20they%20will%20put%20a%20Band-Ai