2C%20women%20looking%20to%20wrap%20their%20heads%20around%20the%20intricacies%20of%20high-interest%20savings%20accounts%20and%20low-cost%20index%20funds%20had%20scant%20few%20options%20that%20spoke%20directly%20to%20them.%20Personal-finance%20education%20in%20US%20high%20schools%20used%20to%20be%20rare%20%E2%80%94%20though%20it's%20gotten%20better%20in%20the%20last%20few%20years%20with%20half%20of%20US%20states%20now%20mandating%20it.%20And%20women-specific%20financial-education%20literature%20tended%20to%20focus%20less%20on%20investing%20in%20real%20estate%20or%20negotiating%20a%20higher%20salary%20than%20on%20learning%20how%20to%20curb%20one's%20spending%20on%20supposedly%20%26quot%3Bfrivolous%26quot%3B%20items%20like%20coffee%2C%20manicures%2C%20and%20haircuts.%20The%20message%2C%20Dunlap%20said%2C%20boiled%20down%20to%3A%20%26quot%3BMen%20get%20to%20be%20millionaires%20by%20making%20more%20money%20and%20being%20the%20fullest%20version%20of%20themselves.%20The%20way%20to%20become%20a%20millionaire%20for%20women%20is%20to%20basically%20hate%20your%20life.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20one%20level%2C%20these%20influencers%20are%20offering%20well-trodden%20financial%20advice%20packaged%20for%20a%20new%20audience%3A%20Dunlap's%20book%20has%20sections%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbanking%2Fwhat-is-an-emergency-fund%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebuilding%20an%20emergency%20fund%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpaid-off-credit-card-debt-solid-plan-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egetting%20out%20of%20debt%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennial-retired-early-financial-independence-fire-strategies-six-figure-income-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einvesting%20for%20retirement%3C%2Fa%3E.%20She%20said%20women%20comprise%2095%25%20of%20her%20audience.%20%26quot%3BWe%20joke%20that%20it's%20largely%20girls%2C%20gays%2C%20and%20theys%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20Sacks%2C%20who%20calls%20herself%20a%20%26quot%3Bzillennial%20finance%20expert%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20that%20her%20content%20is%20aimed%20at%20people%20of%20all%20genders%20but%20that%20women%20tend%20to%20gravitate%20to%20it%20because%20of%20the%20person%20who's%20talking.%20%26quot%3BWe%20all%20have%20the%20same%20message%2C%26quot%3B%20Sacks%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20sort%20of%20like%20finding%20the%20right%20trainer%20who%20motivates%20you.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20influencers%20do%20break%20from%20tradition%20in%20a%20few%20key%20ways.%20Citing%20high%20interest%20rates%2C%20rising%20home%20prices%2C%20and%20a%20booming%20stock%20market%2C%20Sacks%20and%20Dunlap%20have%20made%20the%20case%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frenting-vs-buying-homeownership-wont-make-genz-rich-increase-wealth-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erenting%20instead%20of%20buying%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%20%26quot%3BFinancial%20Feminist%2C%26quot%3B%20Dunlap%20recommends%20readers%20focus%20on%20building%20a%20three-%20to%20six-month%20emergency%20fund%20before%20paying%20off%20debt%20so%20they're%20prepared%20for%20a%20layoff%20or%20dangerous%20home%20situation.%20Sacks%20recommends%20young%20people%20job-hop%20to%20keep%20up%20with%20inflation%20and%20cost-of-living%20increases%20if%20necessary.%20%26quot%3BYou%20should%20be%20making%2015%25%20more%20every%20single%20year%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20if%20you're%20not%20making%20that%20at%20your%20current%20job%2C%20then%20you%20should%20change%20jobs.%26quot%3B%20(%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.epi.org%2Fnominal-wage-tracker%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EResearch%20from%20the%20Economic%20Policy%20Institute%3C%2Fa%3E%20indicates%20that%20since%202007%20US%20employees%20have%20received%20an%20average%20wage%20increase%20of%203.9%25%20a%20year.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERita%20Soledad%20Fern%C3%A1ndez%20Paulino%2C%20a%20California-based%20money%20coach%20and%20creator%20focused%20on%20women%2C%20BIPOC%2C%20and%20LGBTQ%2B%20people%2C%20said%20their%20goal%20is%20to%20help%20people%20become%20%26quot%3Bwork-optional%26quot%3B%20by%20leveraging%20their%20investments.%20%26quot%3BI%20like%20the%20idea%20of%20everyone%20working%20because%20they%20want%20to%20and%20not%20because%20they%20have%20to%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELeah%20Sheppard%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20management%20and%20associate%20dean%20for%20equity%20and%20inclusion%20at%20Washington%20State%20University's%20Carson%20College%20of%20Business%2C%20sees%20this%20wave%20of%20financial%20education%20as%20a%20reflection%20of%20an%20awareness%20among%20Gen%20Zers%20and%20millennials%20that%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Floyalty-employee-employer-job-security-broken-work-companies-bosses-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eboomer-era%20version%20of%20the%20American%20dream%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20where%20you%20work%20your%20way%20up%20the%20ladder%20for%2040%20years%20at%20a%20single%20employer%20and%20put%20away%20enough%20to%20retire%20%E2%80%94%20no%20longer%20applies%20to%20them.%20%26quot%3BYoung%20people%20are%20thinking%2C%20'When%20will%20I%20get%20to%20a%20place%20where%20I%20don't%20really%20have%20to%20worry%20about%20money%3F'%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BIf%20they're%20thinking%2C%20'Traditional%20employment%20is%20not%20working%20well%2C%20I%20don't%20want%20to%20start%20a%20business'%20%E2%80%94%20well%2C%20what's%20the%20other%20way%3F%20And%20it's%20probably%20getting%20really%20smart%20about%20how%20you%20save%20money%2C%20taking%20the%20money%20that%20you%20are%20saving%20and%20investing%20it%20and%20building%20wealth.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESacks%20sees%20it%20as%20a%20matter%20of%20young%20people%20wanting%20to%20take%20the%20future%20into%20their%20own%20hands.%20%26quot%3BYou%20have%20to%20be%20more%20self-reliant%20now%20than%20our%20parents%20ever%20had%20to%20be%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKyla%20Scanlon%2C%20the%20author%20of%20the%202024%20book%20%26quot%3BIn%20This%20Economy%3F%26quot%3B%2C%20sees%20the%20interest%20in%20financial-education%20content%20on%20social%20media%20as%20symptomatic%20of%20a%20curiosity%20about%20alternative%20revenue%20streams%2C%20spurred%20by%20the%20rise%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frobinhood-collapse-what-happened-retail-investing-meme-stocks-future-finance-2022-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efintech%20apps%20like%20Robinhood%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20populist%20financial%20movements%20like%20crypto%20and%20GameStop.%20%26quot%3BPeople%20are%20looking%20at%20the%20market.%20They're%20looking%20at%20different%20income%20sources%2C%20Airbnb%2C%20the%20gigification%20of%20everything%20%E2%80%94%20and%20then%20just%20how%20do%20you%20have%20passive%20income%20outside%20of%20traditional%20income%3F%26quot%3B%20Scanlon%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgambling-young-men-sports-betting-crypto-meme-stock-market-addiction-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eyoung%20men%2C%20this%20often%20takes%20the%20shape%20of%20riskier%20investments%3C%2Fa%3E%20like%20sports%20gambling%2C%20crypto%2C%20and%20meme%20stocks.%20Young%20women%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20are%20turning%20to%20more%20tried-and-true%20tactics.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20survey%20of%202%2C000%20adults%20conducted%20in%20July%202023%2C%20Fidelity%20Investments%20found%20that%20Gen%20Z%20women%20were%20more%20likely%20to%20say%20they%20participated%20in%20the%20stock%20market%20than%20any%20other%20age%20group%2C%20with%2071%25%20of%20women%20ages%2018%20to%2026%20saying%20they%20had%20invested%2C%20compared%20with%2063%25%20of%20millennial%20women%20and%2057%25%20of%20boomer%20women.%20These%20figures%20dovetail%20with%20an%20uptick%20in%20the%20percentage%20of%20people%20under%2035%20who%20held%20stocks%20and%20retirement%20accounts%20in%202022%20compared%20with%202019%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Federal%20Reserve's%20Survey%20of%20Consumer%20Finances%2C%20though%20the%20Fed%20doesn't%20break%20these%20figures%20down%20by%20gender.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EWhether%20the%20goal%20is%20to%20retire%20early%20or%20to%20job-hop%20your%20way%20to%20a%20six-figure%20salary%2C%20this%20wave%20of%20financial%20advice%20departs%20from%20the%20%26quot%3Blean-in%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frise-and-fall-girl-boss-analysis-2020-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Bgirlboss%26quot%3B%20flavor%20of%20feminism%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20dominated%20conversations%20about%20women%20and%20work%20in%20the%202010s.%20%26quot%3BWe're%20just%20more%20disillusioned%20with%20corporate%2C%26quot%3B%20Dunlap%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe're%20more%20disillusioned%20with%20the%20way%20we%20make%20money.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20it's%20advice%20for%20a%20generation%20of%20women%20who%20see%20their%20experiences%20reflected%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flazy-girl-job-is-just-a-healthy-job-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ememes%20like%20the%20%26quot%3Blazy-girl%20job.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20%26quot%3BThe%20lazy-girl%20thing%20is%20just%20like%2C%20'Oh%2C%20give%20me%20a%20little%20bit%20of%20rest%20in%20addition%20to%20my%20work%2C'%26quot%3B%20Dunlap%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20that's%20completely%20reasonable.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20talking%20about%20this%20stuff%20in%20public%20as%20a%20woman%20or%20queer%20person%20can%20be%20fraught.%20Dunlap%20said%20she%20gets%20%26quot%3Bcalled%20every%20insulting%20thing%20you%20can%20call%20a%20woman%20on%20a%20daily%20basis%26quot%3B%20and%20has%20been%20on%20the%20receiving%20end%20of%20death%20threats.%20She%20said%20people%20aren't%20used%20to%20seeing%20women%20talking%20in%20public%20about%20money%2C%20and%20especially%20not%20about%20being%20rich.%20%26quot%3BWe%20have%20different%20expectations%20for%20how%20men%20and%20women%20should%20behave%2C%20especially%20around%20money%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BWomen%20shouldn't%20want%20it.%20You%20should%20be%20grateful%20for%20the%20things%20you%20have.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20women%20BI%20spoke%20with%20said%20they%20faced%20harassment.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20certain%20group%20of%20men%20who%20just%20don't%20like%20women%2C%26quot%3B%20Scanlon%20said.%20But%20for%20the%20most%20part%2C%20the%20influencers%20stressed%20that%20their%20content%20was%20resonating%20with%20the%20people%20it%20was%20supposed%20to%20resonate%20with.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%26quot%3BThe%20comments%20section%20on%20any%20video%20is%20a%20mess%2C%20but%20it's%20also%20the%20most%20supportive%2C%20lovely%20thing%2C%26quot%3B%20Dunlap%20said.%20%26quot%3BSo%20many%20women%2C%20championing%20me%2C%20championing%20each%20other%2C%20championing%20themselves.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20experts%20BI%20spoke%20with%20all%20had%20their%20own%20ways%20of%20describing%20the%20movement.%20Fern%C3%A1ndez%20Paulino%20said%20they%20see%20themself%20as%20belonging%20to%20a%20community%20of%20people%20who%20approach%20money%20and%20finance%20in%20a%20way%20that%20acknowledges%20the%20systemic%20issues%20that%20interfere%20with%20people's%20wealth%20and%20wellness%20%E2%80%94%20such%20as%20the%20economic%20effects%20of%20structural%20racism%20and%20transphobia%2C%20or%20the%20fact%20that%20American%20women%20weren't%20allowed%20to%20own%20a%20credit%20card%20or%20take%20out%20a%20mortgage%20in%20their%20own%20name%20until%20the%201970s.%20%26quot%3BFor%20me%2C%20it's%20like%2C%20I%20can%20have%20wealth%20too.%20You%20can%20have%20wealth%20too.%20It's%20not%20a%20you%20problem%3B%20it's%20a%20we%20problem%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDunlap%20invented%20her%20own%20term%20to%20describe%20it%3A%20financial%20feminism.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20this%20idea%20of%20getting%20yourself%20financially%20to%20a%20point%20where%20you%20are%20stable%2C%20safe%2C%20and%20you%20have%20enough%20wealth%20to%20have%20options%2C%20and%20then%20using%20that%20wealth%20as%20a%20tool%20to%20make%20an%20impact%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20she%20wants%20to%20help%20women%20navigate%20the%20economic%20systems%20we're%20all%20swimming%20in%2C%20so%20they%20can%20help%20other%20women%20by%20changing%20those%20systems%20from%20within.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Femilie-friedlander%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3EEmilie%20Friedlander%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20journalist%20and%20editor%20from%20Brooklyn%2C%20currently%20based%20in%20Philadelphia.%20She%20co-hosts%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheculturejournalist.substack.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3EThe%20Culture%20Journalist%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%2C%20a%20podcast%20about%20culture%20in%20the%20age%20of%20platforms.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-women-personal-finance-investing-stocks-wealth-savings-retirement-2024-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1723455901000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66b63c8bb4912df3ae1a5493%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-women-personal-finance-investing-stocks-wealth-savings-retirement-2024-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Move%20over%2C%20lazy%20girl%20jobs.%20Gen%20Z%20women%20are%20turning%20to%20the%20stock%20market%20to%20get%20rich.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Emilie%20Friedlander)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A6%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22ht