an%20elephants.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20World%20Elephant%20Day%2C%20a%20reflection%20of%20the%20importance%20India%20attaches%20to%20elephants%20is%20found%20in%20the%20fact%20that%20we%20treasure%20it%20as%20our%20National%20Heritage%20Animal.%20It%20is%20a%20matter%20of%20pride%20for%20us%20to%20have%20more%20than%2060%25%20of%20the%20total%20wild%20population%20of%20Asian%20elephants%20in%20India.%20More%20importantly%2C%20the%20elephant%20population%20in%20the%20country%20continues%20to%20be%20stable.%20Under%20the%20Narendra%20Modi-led%20government%2C%20the%20number%20of%20elephant%20reserves%20has%20also%20gone%20up%20to%2033%20and%20the%20area%20under%20Project%20Elephant%20has%20risen%20from%2076%2C508%20sqkm%20to%2080%2C777%20sqkm%2C%20particularly%20over%20the%20last%20decade.%20India%20places%20elephants%20in%20Schedule-1%20of%20the%20Wildlife%20(Protection)%20Act%2C%201972%2C%20according%20the%20highest%20degree%20of%20legal%20protection%20to%20both%20populations%20in%20the%20wild%20and%20elephants%20under%20human%20care.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBeyond%20their%20religious%20and%20cultural%20impact%2C%20it%20is%20worth%20noting%20that%20the%20evolution%20of%20elephants%20is%20very%20similar%20to%20that%20of%20humans.%20Both%20humans%20and%20elephants%20evolved%20around%20the%20same%20time%20in%20ancient%20Africa%20before%20colonising%20most%20of%20the%20world.%20It%20is%20often%20said%20that%20prehistoric%20humans%20often%20followed%20the%20trail%20left%20by%20prehistoric%20elephants%20to%20reach%20new%20places.%20Thus%2C%20elephants%20and%20people%20have%20a%20longstanding%20relationship.%20This%20bond%20has%20acquired%20a%20deeper%20essence%20and%20understanding%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20social%20behaviour%20of%20elephants%20has%20also%20evolved%20remarkably%20similar%20to%20that%20of%20humans.%20The%20elephant%20is%20a%20social%20animal.%20They%20live%20in%20herds%2C%20except%20lone%20tuskers.%20The%20elephant's%20society%20is%20matriarchal%20and%20the%20herds%20are%20mostly%20led%20by%20the%20oldest%20female%20in%20the%20group.%20They%20share%20strong%20bonds%2C%20especially%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20protecting%20young%20calves.%20The%20mother%20elephant%2C%20along%20with%20other%20female%20elephants%2C%20has%20been%20seen%20encircling%20the%20young%20ones%20to%20guard%20against%20looming%20threats%20or%20in%20the%20presence%20of%20large%20carnivores.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.ndtvimg.com%2Fi%2F2017-02%2Fasian-elephant-afp_650x400_41487539955.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EElephants%20live%20long%20and%20possess%20evolved%20and%20strong%20olfactory%20and%20acoustic%20senses.%20They%20are%20said%20to%20have%20the%20'elephantine'%20memory%20as%20well.%20Widely%20known%20for%20expressing%20their%20grief%20or%20trumpeting%20happiness%20in%20celebrations%2C%20elephants%20are%20emotional%20too.%20It%20is%20heart-warming%20to%20see%20them%20bathing%20in%20water%20bodies%2C%20enjoying%20mud%20showers%20and%20wallowing%20in%20swamps.%20Watching%20the%20playful%20young%20ones%20and%20erratic%20lone%20tuskers%20is%20also%20a%20delight.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20important%20to%20recognise%20the%20impact%20of%20elephants%20in%20the%20lives%20of%20innumerable%20flora%20and%20fauna%20in%20the%20forests%20and%20various%20other%20ecosystems%20such%20as%20grasslands%20and%20wetlands.%20While%20moving%20from%20place%20to%20place%20in%20search%20of%20food%20and%20water%2C%20elephants%20invigorate%20the%20life%20cycles%20of%20thousands%20of%20trees%2C%20shrubs%2C%20herbs%2C%20insects%2C%20and%20associated%20mega%20herbivores%20-%20the%20reason%20why%20they%20are%20called%20engineers%20of%20ecosystems.%20Elephants%20have%20far%20larger%20implications%20for%20our%20ecosystems%20and%20are%20the%20true%20keystone%20species%20responsible%20for%20conserving%20our%20biodiversity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFortunately%2C%20India%20has%20more%20than%2025%2C000%20elephants%20in%20four%20major%20regions%20-%20South%2C%20North-Western%2C%20Central-Eastern%20and%20North-Eastern%20-%20of%20their%20inhabitation.%20The%20southern%20region%20has%20the%20largest%20population%20-%20around%2012%2C000%20-%20followed%20by%20the%20northeast%20region%20that%20has%20over%2010%2C000%20elephants.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2019-01%2Fp4drpov8_indian-elephant-generic-istock_625x300_10_January_19.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESeveral%20important%20elephant%20habitats%20in%20the%20country%20have%20been%20notified%20as%20elephant%20reserves.%20A%20total%20of%2033%20elephant%20reserves%20have%20been%20notified%20in%20the%20country%20over%20an%20area%20of%2080%2C777%20square%20km%20spread%20across%2014%20states.%20Led%20by%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%2C%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Environment%2C%20Forest%20and%20Climate%20Change%2C%20in%20coordination%20with%20the%20state%20forest%20departments%2C%20has%20ground%20validated%20150%20elephant%20corridors%20across%2015%20elephant-range%20states%20in%20the%20country%20and%20has%20informed%20the%20state%20governments%20and%20Union%20Territory%20administrations%20to%20take%20necessary%20steps%20to%20protect%20and%20conserve%20the%20elephant%20corridors.%20The%20ministry%20has%20taken%20steps%20to%20strengthen%20the%20management%20of%20elephant%20reserves%20by%20piloting%20a%20management%20effectiveness%20evaluation%20in%20four%20reserves%20and%20establishing%20a%20framework%20for%20conservation%2C%20which%20will%20drive%20scientific%20and%20professional%20management%20of%20India's%20elephant%20reserves.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20elephants%20and%20people%20share%20space%2C%20their%20harmonious%20coexistence%20is%20crucial%20for%20long-term%20survival%20of%20the%20species.%20Reconciling%20human%20welfare%20along%20with%20the%20conservation%20needs%20of%20elephants%20assumes%20priority.%20The%20Modi%20government%20has%20placed%20emphasis%20on%20janbhagidari%20(public%20participation)%20in%20every%20aspect%20of%20elephant%20conservation.%20The%20government%20believes%20active%20participation%20of%20local%20communities%20is%20key%20to%20steering%20elephant%20conservation%20to%20new%20heights.%20All%20of%20us%20here%20have%20a%20collective%20responsibility%20towards%20ensuring%20elephant%20welfare.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20often%20said%2C%20rightly%20so%2C%20that%20one%20cannot%20imagine%20India%20without%20elephants.%20With%20the%20collective%20efforts%20of%20all%20stakeholders%2C%20the%20Modi%20government%20is%20striving%20towards%20securing%20a%20viable%20population%20of%20elephants%20and%20other%20wildlife%20species%20for%20future%20generations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Bhupender%20Yadav%20is%20the%20Union%20Minister%20of%20Environment%2C%20Forest%20and%20Climate%20Change)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1723442880000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-08%2Fbqskohs8_elephants-ani_625x300_12_August_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Felephants-the-engineers-of-ecosystems-6318698%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22On%20World%20Elephant%20Day%2C%20a%20reflection%20of%20the%20importance%20India%20attaches%20to%20elephants%20is%20found%20in%20the%20fact%20that%20we%20treasure%20it%20as%20our%20National%20Heritage%20Animal.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Felephants-the-engineers-of-ecosystems-6318698%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%